<HEAD>Hail Showers in Midwest; Snow in Pacific Northwest</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms that splattered the Midwest with hail continued
today and up to a foot of snow was expected in Oregon and
Washington.
   Hail the size of golf balls fell Tuesday across Wisconsin,
Minnesota, Iowa and the Dakotas, and thunderstorms whipped winds up
to 70 mph, downing large tree limbs at Glen Ullin, N.D.
   Thunderstorms extended this morning from northeastern Nebraska
across Iowa to Wisconsin, and in western North Dakota.
   A severe storm watch was in effect for parts of the Dakotas,
southern Iowa and northeastern Missouri.
   Heavy weather also hit the middle Atlantic Coast on Tuesday.
   High winds downed power lines at Kenly, N.C., and golf
ball-sized hail fell at Greenville, with nickel-sized hail at
Gatesville.
   Showers and thunderstorms drenched New England and western
Pennsylvania this morning, with storms developing in the central
Gulf ahead of the same cold front.
   Scattered showers fell in the Northwest, with snow in the higher
elevations of the Cascade mountains. Weather service advisories
said up to a foot of snow was possible.
   Gusty winds swept the deserts of southern California, southeast
Wyoming and eastern Colorado.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 30
degrees at Yellowstone Park, Wyo., to 88 degrees at Phoenix, Ariz.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstorms
from the upper Great Lakes to the central Plains; severe
thunderstorms from Kansas to Michigan; scattered showers from the
northern Pacific to the Rockies; showers and thunderstorms from New
England into the middle Atlantic region; and strong and gusty winds
over the Rockies.
   Highs were expected to be in the 60s and 70s from northern
California through the Rockies and northern Plains to the upper
Great Lakes and on the Atlantic coast; in the 50s across the
Pacific Northwest and northern Rockies; between 100 and 105 from
Arizona to western Texas; and in the 80s or 90s elsewhere.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 60 fair; Boston 59 cloudy; Buffalo 53 drizzle;
Charleston, S.C. 69 fair; Cincinnati 55 fair; Cleveland 54 foggy;
Detroit 50 fair; Miami 76 fair; New York 61 drizzle; Philadelphia
62 foggy; Pittsburgh 56 foggy; Portland, Me. 55 cloudy; Washington
62 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 57 thunderstorm; Chicago 68 cloudy;
Dallas-Fort Worth 77 fair; Denver 62 fair; Des Moines 63
thunderstorm; Indianapolis 57 fair; Kansas City 74 fair;
Minneapolis-St. Paul 64 fair; Nashville 57 fair; New Orleans 76
cloudy; St. Louis 68 cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 75 partly cloudy; Anchorage 47 partly cloudy;
Las Vegas 77 windy; Los Angeles 57 fair; Phoenix 86 fair; Salt Lake
City 53 partly cloudy; San Diego 61 fair; San Francisco 53 fair;
Seattle 46 partly cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 59 cloudy; Toronto 57 cloudy.
