<HEAD>Newspaper Says Girl Wanted to Blackmail Rob Lowe</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 17-year-old girl whom Rob Lowe is accused of
filming in a pornographic videotape bragged to friends that she
planned to blackmail the star for $2 million, a newspaper reported
today.
   The Atlanta Journal-Constitution cited an affidavit filed last
summer in Superior Court in the divorce of the girl's parents.
   The girl's mother filed a lawsuit May 12 seeking unspecified
damages from Lowe, the Brat Pack star of such movies as ``About
Last Night'' and ``St. Elmo's Fire.''
   District Attorney Lewis Slaton said Lowe, 24, could face
criminal charges for exploitation of a minor. The girl was 16 at
the time of the alleged incident.
   Documents filed in the lawsuit over the videotape have been
sealed, but newspaper lawyers argued Tuesday that they should be
made public.
   News reports have said that the girl, who turned 17 in April,
met Lowe at a nightclub in Atlanta during last summer's Democratic
National Convention.
   According to an affidavit from an acquaintance of the girl, the
teen-ager said she and another woman had sex with Lowe and ``they
all took turns filming each other,'' the newspaper reported.
   Another affidavit, from the girl's next-door neighbor, alleges
the girl planned to use the video to blackmail Lowe for $2 million,
the newspaper said.
   Lowe's public relations firm Tuesday said the actor has no
comment ``until the matter is resolved.''
   Judge Jerry W. Baxter closed the court record on the lawsuit
shortly after it was filed because ``the harm otherwise resulting
to the privacy of the parties in interest clearly outweighs the
public interest.''
   A hearing on the newspapers' request for access to the documents
has not been set.
