<SECOND>PM-Sexual Assault,0220</SECOND>
<HEAD>Glen Ridge Students Arrested for Sex Assault of Girl</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEWARK, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Five teen-agers were arrested today on
charges they sexually assaulted a 17-year-old mentally retarded
girl, police said.
   Eight other teen-age males witnessed the hour-long attack March
1, and other arrests are possible, said Essex County Prosecutor
Herbert Tate.
   ``We are satisfied that this was a nonconsensual sexual assault
by these five males against this young woman,'' Tate said at a news
conference. ``She didn't understand the nature and quality of her
actions.''
   Tate said the high school students met the girl in a park in
Glen Ridge, an affluent New York City suburb, then went with her to
the home of two of the students, 18-year-old twins Kevin and Kyle
Scherzer, whose parents were not home.
   Tate said the girl was assaulted in the basement with a small
baseball bat and a broomstick. There was no sexual intercourse, he
said.
   He said the students and the girl knew each other, and the
youths knew she was retarded.
   All five awaited a court hearing today.
   The Scherzer brothers and Peter Quigley, 18, were arrested on
conspirary and sexual assault charges, and a 17-year-old and
another student who has since turned 18 were charged with juvenile
delinquency, Tate said.
