<HEAD>United Plane Overshoots Runway</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: INSERTS one graf before last to ADD that cause unknown.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A United Airlines jet carrying 203 people
overshot a runway and rolled a short distance into the grass at
O'Hare International Airport today, authorities said. No injuries
were reported.
   The nosegear of the DC-10 from Philadelphia went about 10 feet
past the end of the runway after an otherwise normal landing, said
United spokeswoman Sara Dornacker.
   Everyone aboard left by mobile staircases and were taken by bus
to the terminal, she said. Evacuation chutes were not used, she
said.
   The cause of the mishap was not known, Ms. Dornacker said.
   The runway was closed while plane was removed.
