<SECOND>AM-Obit-Jasperson,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>AIDS Victim Who Sued Nail Salon Dies Of Disease</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Paul Jasperson, who sued a nail salon two
years ago claiming he was refused a pedicure there because he
suffered from AIDS, has died of the disease, his attorney said. He
was 37.
   Jasperson, who died May 15, filed suit against Jessica's Nail
Salon in January 1987, contending the business violated a West
Hollywood ordinance that prohibited discrimination against people
with AIDS.
   A court found the salon did refuse the pedicure, but refused to
issue an injunction barring such action.
   Jasperson's attorney, Gloria Allred, said Monday she would
pursue an appeal on his behalf.
   Ms. Allred said Jasperson proceeded with the lawsuit ``at great
risk to his own health ... in order to help win rights for others.''
   Jasperson is survived by his parents and two brothers. A
memorial service is scheduled Saturday.
</TEXT>
