<HEAD>United Plane Slides Off Runway</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A United Airlines jet carrrying 203 people slid
off a runway and rolled onto grass Wednesday after landing at
O'Hare International Airport, officials said.
   There were no injuries or damage, according to spokeswomen with
the city's aviation department and United.
   The nose of the DC-10 from Philadelphia went about 10 feet past
the end of the runway after an otherwise normal landing, Sara
Dornacker of United said.
   Rain on a newly painted portion of the runway apparently
contributed to the slide, she said.
   Everyone aboard left the craft by mobile staircases, Ms.
Dornacker said. Evacuation chutes were not used.
   The runway, closed while the plane was removed, opened about an
hour after the 8:52 a.m. incident, according to the Federal
Aviation Administration.
   The plane was back in service Wednesday afternoon, Ms. Dornacker
said.
