<FIRST>r a AM-SEPTA-ConrailWreck     05-24 0116</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-SEPTA-Conrail Wreck,0118</SECOND>
<HEAD>Conrail Coal Car Smashes Into Pennsylvania Commuter Train</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A runaway Conrail car loaded with coal
smashed into a passenger train returning from the airport
Wednesday, injuring at least 17 people, officials said.
   The coal car collided with the single-car airport train at 5:18
p.m., according to Donna Alson of the Southeastern Pennsylvania
Transportation Authority. The engineer threw the train into reverse
but was unable to outrun the coal car, SEPTA spokeswoman Pat Fallon
said.
   The coal car broke loose from a string of standing cars,
according to Conrail spokeswoman Pat Linsey. She said Conrail was
investigating the accident.
   The injured were treated at hospitals and released, hospital
spokeswomen said.
</TEXT>
