<FIRST>r i AM-NutDeath     05-24 0216</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Nut Death,0223</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man With Nut Allergy Dies After Eating Brazil Nut and Almond</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KAMLOOPS, British Columbia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Dallas man who was allergic
to nuts died after eating a Brazil nut and an almond he was given
by a female companion, authorities said.
   Darryl Reid, 38, ate the nuts Monday while driving near Heffley
Creek just north of here and about 270 miles northeast of
Vancouver, said Coroner Bob Graham.
   When Reid and the woman, whom Graham did not identify, stopped
for gas, she bought a bag of nuts and began eating them as they
resumed driving, the coroner said.
   ``She offered him a Brazil nut,'' said Graham. ``Then she
offered him an almond.
   ``Then he turned to her and told her `I'm allergic to nuts.' ''
   They returned to Heffley Creek, but by the time an ambulance
arrived, Reid's heart had stopped from the allergic reaction, said
Graham.
   He said he knew of only one other similar case in the region, a
youth who died five minutes after eating a chocolate bar containing
nuts.
   Reid apparently offered no explanation to the woman, a casual
acquaintance, for eating the nuts.
   ``I guess he was just driving along with his mind in neutral,''
said Graham. ``They were offered to him and he took them.''
</TEXT>
