Anglican-Roman Catholic liturgy marking the Church of England's
l6th century closing of the famous abbey here and other monasteries.
   The affair was canceled after Roman Catholic Bishop Augustine
Harris, who had been on the planning committee, withdrew from
participation, saying a celebrative note was being applied to a sad
event.
   Anglican Bishop Gordon Bates said of the cancellation: ``You
can't have a service of reconciliation, penitence and hope for the
future if part won't play ball. It would be a sham.''
