<HEAD>Sears Campaign Will Promote NBC Fall Shows</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   NBC is teaming with Sears for a promotional
campaign for its fall program schedule similar to that announced
recently by CBS and K mart.
   The NBC-Sears campaign will offer weekly contests in which the
winners will be flown to Hollywood for ``instant stardom.'' They
will appear on NBC prime-time shows and in promotional spots for
the network.
   The four weekly contests will begin on Labor Day, it was
announced Tuesday by John Miller, senior vice president of NBC
Entertainment, and Thomas E. Morris, vice president of marketing
for Sears Merchandise Group.
   Miller said it was ``the largest and most exciting promotion in
network history.''
   Each weekly winner, beginning Sept. 3, will receive a part in an
NBC prime-time show and transportation for two to Los Angeles. They
will also receive use of a limousine, a deluxe hotel suite, a
``beauty makeover,'' shopping sprees, a luxury automobile and
$10,000 in cash.
   Other prizes include automobiles, television sets, airline
tickets, Sears gift certificates and NBC merchandise worth $2
million.
   People can enter the contest by answering questions about NBC
programs in a questionnaire that will appear in Sears advertising
supplements. Sears will also mail an eight-page brochure about
NBC's shows to 20 million customers with Sears charge cards.
