<HEAD>Zale Agrees to Acquire Gordon Jewelry</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Zale Corp., the world's largest jeweler, has
agreed to acquire Gordon Jewelry Corp. for about $312 million, the
companies said Wednesday.
   Gordon officials said Zale will pay $36.75 a share for all
outstanding shares of the Houston-based jeweler.
   Gordon stockholders owning approximately 54 percent of the
outstanding shares have agreed to tender all of their shares to
Zale, according to the announcement.
   Zale said it already owns about 4.2 percent of Gordon's 8.5
million outstanding shares.
   ``We believe the transaction provides excellent value for our
stockholders and are extremely pleased with the result,'' said
Gordon President Daniel P. Gordon.
   Zale, which is equally owned by Peoples Jewellers Ltd. of
Toronto and Swarovski International Holding A.G. of Switzerland,
called the deal a positive step.
   ``We are proud and pleased to be acquiring Gordon, and will
strive to maintain its traditions and fine reputation in the
communities it serves,'' Zale President Irving R. Gerstein said.
