<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices closed slightly higher in moderate,
uneventful trading today with little news to spur investors.
   The market opened lower behind weakening bond prices after the
Bank of England said it would raise its base lending rate from 13
percent to 14 percent.
   Stocks began to firm slightly after midday taking a cue from
rising bond prices, then moved narrowly for the remainder of the
session.
   ``The market was pretty uneventful overall,'' said Eugene
Peroni, technical analyst with Janney Montgomery Scott.
   Analysts said the market spent most of the day in a
consolidation phase with some investors taking profits amid mostly
even-keeled buying and selling.
