natural for the market to pause for rest and relaxation,'' said
Dennis Jarrett, technical analyst with Kidder, Peabody Group Inc.
   Despite concern on Tuesday that the dollar was rising too fast
against Japanese and European currencies, many analysts said the
market continued to view the strengthening U.S. dollar as positive.
   The dollar advanced against the Japanese yen as well as against
major European currencies.
   The stocks of potential takeover targets, such as Avon, were
active. Oil stocks as well as steel and high tech issues also
showed broad-based gains.
